          0,
          " piece delves deep into their thinking:"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "blockquote",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "‚ÄúIt might be cheesy to say, because I‚Äôve now said it a bunch of times, but I feel like the worst part about social media is that it‚Äôs social,‚Äù Systrom says. ‚ÄúI think the ‚Äòsocial‚Äô part of social media ‚Äî for a long time, in terms of information consumption ‚Äî has been a hack to filter for information that would be interesting to you. But we now don‚Äôt need that hack, because we can learn what‚Äôs interesting to you,‚Äù he continues. ‚ÄúWe can quantify it. We can build profiles. And then we can serve you content that is both high-quality, balanced and interesting to you.‚Äù"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "What‚Äôs also interesting is that they see the app as a very selective place for news. You‚Äôre not going to find news from every site on the web in there, but a tight selection curated by the team:"
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "blockquote",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "‚ÄúWhen I say taste, I mean the top of the funnel in our system ‚Äî the publishers we choose to distribute,‚Äù notes Systrom. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs not a free-for-all. We don‚Äôt crawl the entire web and just let everything go in.‚Äù"
        ]
